(a) ‘access control mechanism’ means any measure, including a technical measure,
through which access to online curated content may be restricted based on
verification of the identity or age of a user;
(b) ‘access services’ means any measure, including technical measure such as closed
captioning, subtitles and audio descriptions, through which the accessibility of
online curated content may be improved for persons with disabilities;
(c) ‘Act’ means the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);
(d) ‘child’ means any person below the age of eighteen years;
(e) ‘committee’ means the Inter-Departmental Committee constituted under rule 14;
(f) ‘communication link’ means a connection between a hypertext or graphical
element, and one or more items in the same or different electronic document
wherein upon clicking on a hyperlinked item, the user is automatically transferred
to the other end of the hyperlink which can be another electronic record or another
